WEBVTT

00:05.537 --> 00:06.772
[LYNN] <i>You have to stop.</i>

00:06.775 --> 00:09.772
I can't keep letting you put
yourself, or me through this.

00:09.775 --> 00:11.108
I promise...

00:12.125 --> 00:13.191
no more.

00:13.193 --> 00:14.559
[JEFFERSON] <i>It has been nine years</i>

00:14.561 --> 00:16.739
<i>since I've even come
close to using my powers.</i>

00:16.742 --> 00:19.030
[GAMBI] <i>Do you remember
why you became Black Lightning?</i>

00:19.032 --> 00:20.687
You wanted to give the people hope.

00:21.701 --> 00:23.568
[ANISSA] <i>Somebody has to do something,</i>

00:23.570 --> 00:26.871
<i>because all of this policing,
and marching, and praying,</i>

00:26.873 --> 00:28.573
it hasn't changed anything.

00:30.957 --> 00:32.093
[GRUNTING]

00:33.780 --> 00:36.087
[JEFFERSON] <i>It is time that people know</i>

00:36.090 --> 00:37.815
<i>that Black Lightning...</i>

00:39.385 --> 00:40.451
<i>is back.</i>

00:42.453 --> 00:44.387
[NARRATOR] <i>Previously on</i> Black Lightning...

00:48.625 --> 00:49.894
It's my breathing.

00:49.896 --> 00:51.929
- Wanna be my girlfriend?
- Yeah.

00:54.501 --> 00:55.900
[ANISSA] <i>I'm Anissa.</i>

00:55.902 --> 00:57.361
Grace.

00:57.364 --> 01:01.605
Yeah, I... I saved more lives
as the principal of Garfield High

01:01.608 --> 01:03.407
than I ever did as Black Lightning.

01:03.409 --> 01:04.941
- It's true.
- It's a lie!

01:04.944 --> 01:07.345
LaWanda is dead. But
I could've saved her.

01:09.202 --> 01:10.401
You'll be ready.

01:10.404 --> 01:11.469
[LALA] Damn, boss.

01:11.472 --> 01:12.884
[TOBIAS] <i>If the people of Freeland start</i>

01:12.886 --> 01:14.474
<i>to perceive we are no longer in control,</i>

01:14.476 --> 01:16.117
<i>then they won't fear us.</i>

01:16.120 --> 01:18.022
And I surely can't have that.

01:18.854 --> 01:20.421
For all you lost, Lady Eve.

01:21.117 --> 01:22.835
Take Reverend Holt, for instance.

01:22.838 --> 01:23.871
[MEN CHANTING] Freedom!

01:23.874 --> 01:25.524
[LADY EVE] <i>He's planning a march.</i>

01:25.527 --> 01:28.095
<i>I don't mind people believing in God.</i>

01:28.098 --> 01:33.104
They just can't believe that
they can take back these streets.

01:34.407 --> 01:35.673
[GROANS]

01:35.675 --> 01:37.375
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

01:37.378 --> 01:39.010
[GROANS]

01:39.012 --> 01:40.207
[ANISSA GASPS]

01:42.282 --> 01:43.981
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

01:43.983 --> 01:45.316
[STUDENT 1] Hey, what's going on?

01:45.318 --> 01:47.718
[STUDENT 2] Oh, my God! Do
you guys hear that? Who is he?

01:47.721 --> 01:48.920
[STUDENT 1] What is going on?

01:48.923 --> 01:50.556
Principal Pierce! Principal Pierce!

01:50.559 --> 01:52.875
There's someone freaking
out in the boy's bathroom.

01:52.878 --> 01:54.664
Okay, find Vice Principal Fowdy.

01:54.667 --> 01:57.134
Tell her I said to get
security over here now.

01:57.137 --> 01:58.570
[SCHOOL BELL RINGS]

01:58.573 --> 02:00.440
Get to class. Get to class.

02:01.501 --> 02:03.534
[BOY SCREAMING]

02:05.738 --> 02:07.772
[GRUNTING]

02:07.774 --> 02:09.582
Bernard?

02:09.585 --> 02:10.751
[SCREAMS]

02:10.753 --> 02:12.620
Come on, Bernard, talk to me.

02:12.623 --> 02:13.956
[PANTING]

02:15.065 --> 02:16.464
Principal Pierce?

02:18.371 --> 02:19.684
I don't know what happened.

02:19.686 --> 02:21.185
We can talk about that later.

02:21.187 --> 02:22.753
[GRUNTING]

02:22.755 --> 02:24.589
You scared me half to death.

02:24.591 --> 02:27.024
[GRUNTING AND GROANING]

02:27.026 --> 02:28.159
Bernard?

02:28.161 --> 02:29.360
[GRUNTING]

02:32.504 --> 02:33.731
Bernard!

02:37.237 --> 02:38.603
[EFFORT GRUNTS]

02:40.000 --> 02:46.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:08.747 --> 03:09.934
[DOOR OPENS]

03:13.006 --> 03:14.505
- You okay?
- Yeah.

03:14.507 --> 03:16.574
What the hell did that boy take?

03:20.580 --> 03:22.446
[HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING ON STEREO]

03:34.360 --> 03:36.027
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

03:38.398 --> 03:39.597
[LOWERS VOLUME]

03:44.570 --> 03:46.337
[BOY] Let's go. All right.

03:47.607 --> 03:49.847
[LISA] I mean, I wanna try
it, but I'm, I'm kinda scared.

03:51.244 --> 03:52.343
[MUSIC STOPS]

03:52.981 --> 03:54.645
Lisa. Neema.

03:55.648 --> 03:57.872
Oh, no, it's Harriet Tubman.

03:57.875 --> 03:59.650
- Get away from them.
- Ms. Pierce?

03:59.652 --> 04:00.751
Get in the car.

04:00.754 --> 04:02.087
Now.

04:03.463 --> 04:04.662
[SIGHS]

04:06.841 --> 04:09.755
How do you sleep at night selling
that junk to your own people?

04:09.758 --> 04:11.028
I sleep fine.

04:11.030 --> 04:12.630
You better stay away from my students.

04:12.632 --> 04:14.198
Or what?

04:20.540 --> 04:22.373
- That bitch crazy, man.
- Shh.

04:22.375 --> 04:23.808
What did you say?

04:23.810 --> 04:25.343
You heard me, bitch!

04:47.699 --> 04:49.349
I found these on my student.

04:49.352 --> 04:51.986
And he was so out of control
that the only way I could keep him

04:51.989 --> 04:55.190
from hurting anyone
was to blast him. Twice.

04:55.193 --> 04:57.935
Must be this new drug, Green
Light, I've been hearing about.

04:57.938 --> 05:00.444
First Jennifer and Anissa get kidnapped,

05:00.446 --> 05:02.279
then Reverend Holt and Khalil get shot,

05:02.281 --> 05:05.116
and now one of my
students damn near OD's.

05:05.119 --> 05:08.251
It's like this city is under
attack, and we're losing.

05:08.254 --> 05:10.354
You only lose if you stop fighting.

05:10.356 --> 05:11.922
But you can't save everyone, Jeff.

05:11.924 --> 05:13.157
You're just gonna have to accept that.

05:13.159 --> 05:14.771
We need to go hard at The One Hundred.

05:14.774 --> 05:15.739
You sure it's them?

05:15.742 --> 05:17.669
Who else would be dealing in Freeland?

05:17.672 --> 05:19.989
One Hundred have got
their hands in everything.

05:19.992 --> 05:21.232
We could waste a lot of time

05:21.234 --> 05:22.800
going after the wrong
part of their business.

05:22.802 --> 05:24.630
I know all the street-level guys,

05:24.633 --> 05:26.404
but I don't know any of the higher-ups.

05:26.406 --> 05:28.172
I'll reach out to my contacts.

05:28.174 --> 05:30.341
Okay. And after I check
in with the family,

05:30.343 --> 05:31.825
I'm gonna hit the streets tonight.

05:31.828 --> 05:33.110
See what I can find out.

05:33.113 --> 05:34.950
Sounds like a full night.

05:37.106 --> 05:38.263
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

05:38.266 --> 05:39.483
[JEFFERSON] What'd you hear?

05:39.485 --> 05:40.751
[MAN GRUNTING]

05:40.753 --> 05:42.219
Where can I find him?

05:44.099 --> 05:46.357
I told you, I don't know
nothing about no Green Light.

05:46.359 --> 05:48.708
Yeah, well, you better
tell me something.

05:48.711 --> 05:50.361
'Cause I ain't in the
best of moods, bruh.

05:50.363 --> 05:51.629
Snitches get...

05:53.794 --> 05:55.127
[GROANING]

05:55.130 --> 05:56.567
Snitches get what?

05:56.569 --> 05:57.535
[PANTING]

05:57.537 --> 05:58.803
Who do you work for?

05:58.805 --> 05:59.937
I ain't telling you nothing.

05:59.939 --> 06:01.114
All right.

06:01.117 --> 06:03.297
I can do this all night.

06:03.300 --> 06:07.091
So one way or the other,
you gonna tell me something.

06:07.094 --> 06:09.227
Okay! Okay, okay. Okay.

06:11.250 --> 06:12.416
Two-Bits.

06:13.638 --> 06:15.027
Two-Bits?

06:15.030 --> 06:18.155
I know it sounds like a '70s slave
name, but that's what he go by.

06:19.969 --> 06:21.202
Where can I find him?

06:21.205 --> 06:22.959
Tanner's Taproom on 7th.

06:22.962 --> 06:24.261
All right.

06:25.531 --> 06:26.730
Say good night.

06:28.471 --> 06:33.560
