06:37.754 --> 06:39.243
[LADY EVE] Tobias...

06:39.246 --> 06:40.996
did you know that in Africa

06:40.999 --> 06:45.416
some people believe
that albinos are magical?

06:45.418 --> 06:49.254
These people will actually
kidnap random albinos,

06:49.257 --> 06:51.574
cut them up, grind their bones,

06:51.577 --> 06:54.490
and sell it as magic dust.

06:54.493 --> 06:56.726
Yes, I'm aware of that.

06:56.729 --> 06:59.663
I admire how you reinvented yourself

06:59.665 --> 07:03.834
after you lost your
career as a politician.

07:03.836 --> 07:08.172
You went underground, built
a whole new career with us,

07:08.174 --> 07:12.143
and, when we rewarded
you with The One Hundred,

07:12.145 --> 07:13.511
you did a good job.

07:13.513 --> 07:15.212
- But?
- But...

07:15.215 --> 07:18.682
ever since Black Lightning
returned to Freeland,

07:18.684 --> 07:22.486
my partners have become less confident

07:22.488 --> 07:25.022
in your ability to lead The One Hundred.

07:28.094 --> 07:30.402
Is there something
you would like to say?

07:30.405 --> 07:33.689
I've literally made
you millions of dollars,

07:33.692 --> 07:36.567
and you giving me a hard
time over one mistake?

07:36.569 --> 07:38.435
But it isn't one mistake.

07:39.338 --> 07:41.657
It's your reputation.

07:41.660 --> 07:44.808
Your entire criminal career
was built on the belief

07:44.810 --> 07:48.520
that you killed Black
Lightning nine years ago,

07:48.523 --> 07:53.645
when nobody else could. It's...
it's like you lied on your resume.

07:53.648 --> 07:56.887
Black Lightning's death
was your calling card,

07:56.890 --> 08:01.993
and now people are beginning to
feel like they've been deceived,

08:01.996 --> 08:04.497
and it's messing with my bottom line.

08:04.500 --> 08:06.965
I got people paying up on protection,

08:06.968 --> 08:09.692
and that's offsetting any lost revenue.

08:09.695 --> 08:13.145
And I'm gonna take Black
Lightning out, once and for all.

08:13.148 --> 08:16.168
How am I supposed to believe

08:16.171 --> 08:18.621
that you can take out
Black Lightning now,

08:18.624 --> 08:20.678
when you couldn't take him out then?

08:20.680 --> 08:25.082
And on top of that, you're
making a lot of noise.

08:26.185 --> 08:28.919
Your men shot a reverend

08:28.921 --> 08:31.137
and paralyzed a kid.

08:31.140 --> 08:33.791
They were talking about that
kid going to the Olympics.

08:33.793 --> 08:35.326
He wasn't going to no Olympics.

08:35.328 --> 08:37.418
Well, he isn't now.

08:37.421 --> 08:39.221
And that's for sure.

08:40.566 --> 08:44.363
You... You need to take
Black Lightning out,

08:44.366 --> 08:47.657
and button this thing up quick.

08:47.660 --> 08:50.174
I'm not gonna tell you
how to run your crew,

08:50.176 --> 08:53.210
but if I were you, I
would use some of that

08:53.212 --> 08:56.213
albino magic to get it done.

08:57.149 --> 08:59.657
Because if you don't,

08:59.660 --> 09:03.454
my partners are gonna
turn you into dust.

09:06.199 --> 09:07.932
Do you understand?

09:09.098 --> 09:10.461
Yes.

09:10.463 --> 09:11.662
Good.

09:13.132 --> 09:14.865
[LADY EVE HUMMING]

09:31.964 --> 09:34.684
I'm glad to see you're
back on your feet, Bernard.

09:37.018 --> 09:38.551
How you feeling?

09:38.554 --> 09:39.720
He's fine.

09:41.874 --> 09:44.107
You know you really gave me a scare.

09:45.077 --> 09:46.939
Yeah, I know.

09:46.942 --> 09:48.637
Look, I'm sorry.

09:49.815 --> 09:51.748
We got an e-mail from the board.

09:51.750 --> 09:54.017
Says Bernard's gonna get expelled.

09:54.967 --> 09:56.933
We wanted to ask for a second chance.

09:56.936 --> 09:59.220
Bernard's never been in any trouble,

09:59.223 --> 10:02.459
and he just got acceptance
letters from four colleges.

10:02.461 --> 10:05.028
This is gonna mess everything up.

10:05.030 --> 10:06.934
Bernard's not going anywhere...

10:06.937 --> 10:08.670
but to college.

10:10.281 --> 10:12.581
- I promise.
- Thank you.

10:14.072 --> 10:18.875
Now, Bernard, um, I do need to
know where you got those drugs.

10:18.877 --> 10:20.977
Come on, Mr. Pierce, I ain't no snitch.

10:20.979 --> 10:23.680
Yes, you are. Tell him.

10:27.019 --> 10:31.728
[SIGHS] I, uh, I got it from
this dude in the neighborhood,

10:31.731 --> 10:33.924
uh, Ronald Wright.

10:34.893 --> 10:36.927
He said the first taste was free.

10:45.504 --> 10:48.002
- Where's the future?
- It's right here.

10:48.005 --> 10:49.504
Whose life is this?

10:50.842 --> 10:51.908
It's mine.

10:51.910 --> 10:53.610
What're you gonna do with it?

10:53.613 --> 10:55.446
I'mma live it by any means necessary.

10:55.449 --> 10:56.518
What're you gonna do with it?

10:56.520 --> 10:58.856
I'mma live it by any means necessary.

11:02.054 --> 11:03.715
We're gonna figure this out.

11:05.290 --> 11:07.257
- Thank you, Principal Pierce.
- Yeah.

11:10.128 --> 11:11.194
Thank you.

11:11.196 --> 11:12.562
You're welcome.

11:18.760 --> 11:21.294
The board will never let
Bernard stay at Garfield.

11:21.297 --> 11:23.380
The bylaws clearly state
that it's my decision.

11:23.383 --> 11:25.842
You know, you seem a bit more concerned

11:25.844 --> 11:27.711
about what the board wants
than what's good for these kids.

11:27.713 --> 11:30.981
Tell the board that it's my
decision and my decision alone.

11:30.983 --> 11:34.368
I care about Garfield as much as you,

11:34.371 --> 11:37.108
and I'm the vice principal,
not your secretary.

11:37.111 --> 11:38.864
So if you want the board
to know something,

11:38.865 --> 11:40.865
you should tell them yourself.

11:51.003 --> 11:52.535
[INDISTINCT CHATTER ON RADIO]

11:52.537 --> 11:53.737
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

11:53.739 --> 11:54.738
Yeah?

11:54.740 --> 11:57.340
The drugs that came into the school

11:57.342 --> 11:59.642
came from a guy named Ronald Wright.

11:59.644 --> 12:01.411
<i>- Really?</i>
- What?

12:01.413 --> 12:03.646
I'm looking at Mr.
Wright's body right now.

12:03.648 --> 12:05.148
<i>What do you mean his body?</i>

12:05.150 --> 12:07.527
He's dead. OD'd on Green Light.

12:07.530 --> 12:09.345
Evidently, Mr. Wright didn't follow the

12:09.348 --> 12:11.160
number one rule of being a drug dealer,

12:11.163 --> 12:13.447
"Don't get high on your own supply."

12:13.450 --> 12:15.725
What'd you get from
that dealer last night?

12:15.727 --> 12:18.081
His distributor is
a guy named Two-Bits.

12:18.084 --> 12:20.017
[CHUCKLES] Is that like Huggy Bear?

12:20.020 --> 12:22.332
[CHUCKLES] You got jokes today.

12:22.334 --> 12:24.934
You know things are bad
when drug dealers are OD-ing.

12:24.936 --> 12:27.837
I actually know Two-Bits.
I grew up with him.

12:27.839 --> 12:30.940
I mean, he was a bit younger than me,

12:30.942 --> 12:32.509
but I used to know him pretty well.

12:32.511 --> 12:34.044
What're you thinking?

12:34.046 --> 12:37.528
I'm thinking this is gonna get a
lot worse before it gets better.

12:40.063 --> 12:41.996
- [KHALIL GRUNTING]
- [NURSE] Easy.

12:43.955 --> 12:46.333
Easy. Easy. Easy.

12:47.659 --> 12:49.088
Good job.

12:49.091 --> 12:50.427
[SIGHS]

12:50.429 --> 12:51.661
You okay?

12:51.664 --> 12:54.230
Yeah. Yeah. This is easy.

12:54.232 --> 12:55.698
[CHUCKLES]

12:55.700 --> 12:57.403
All right, I'll get you a towel.

12:59.319 --> 13:02.320
[NURSE 1] I don't know why they're
leading that boy on like that.

13:02.323 --> 13:03.920
[NURSE 2] There's a
chance he might walk.

13:03.922 --> 13:06.923
[NURSE 1] His spinal cord was
nearly severed. Why get his hopes up?

13:06.926 --> 13:08.783
[NURSE 2] It's a shame. He's so young.

13:08.786 --> 13:09.985
Hey!

13:09.988 --> 13:11.713
What the hell is your problem?

13:11.716 --> 13:13.083
What?

13:13.879 --> 13:15.278
He can hear you.

13:16.221 --> 13:17.387
I'm sorry.

13:23.553 --> 13:24.944
You okay?

13:24.947 --> 13:26.662
Yeah.

13:26.665 --> 13:29.257
Look, it don't matter what
they think. They don't know me.

13:30.039 --> 13:31.672
I'mma be all right.

13:32.867 --> 13:34.299
Yeah, I know.

13:35.540 --> 13:37.207
I know you will.

13:48.320 --> 13:49.486
[SOBBING]

13:59.998 --> 14:01.331
[GROANING]

14:02.122 --> 14:05.400
You lied to me. You told
me Black Lightning was dead.

14:05.403 --> 14:07.426
You said you personally saw the body.

14:07.429 --> 14:09.105
I thought... I mean, I saw...

14:09.107 --> 14:11.674
Look, I don't have time for
your lies. What happened?

14:11.676 --> 14:14.377
The body came out of the river
where Black Lightning fell.

14:14.379 --> 14:16.138
How many people could've
fallen into that river?

14:16.140 --> 14:17.039
I thought it was him.

14:17.042 --> 14:18.609
What do you mean you thought?

14:18.612 --> 14:21.842
My boss put the body from
the river in the crematorium.

14:21.845 --> 14:23.832
Was he dressed like
Earth, Wind and Fire?

14:23.835 --> 14:25.355
What? [GRUNTS]

14:25.357 --> 14:28.548
Was the body your boss put in the
fire dressed like Maurice White?

14:28.551 --> 14:29.910
[CHUCKLES]

14:29.913 --> 14:33.096
Did you personally see Black
Lightning's body burn or not?

14:34.199 --> 14:36.399
My entire situation's in jeopardy,

14:36.401 --> 14:39.402
because you didn't do
what you was paid to do.

14:40.539 --> 14:43.406
You were supposed to confirm
Black Lightning's death.

14:43.409 --> 14:45.890
Well, since Black Lightning ain't dead,

14:47.512 --> 14:48.912
you owe me a death.

14:48.914 --> 14:54.384
What? No. No. No. No!

14:54.387 --> 14:55.952
[GRUNTING]

15:05.976 --> 15:08.643
Mmm-mmm. Come in here, young lady.

15:09.515 --> 15:12.085
Well, the main reason
you have that phone

15:12.088 --> 15:14.285
is so that when we need
to contact you, we can.

15:14.288 --> 15:16.913
I'm... I'm sorry. It died
when I was visiting Khalil.

15:16.916 --> 15:18.988
Well, your coach called
us to see if you were okay.

15:18.991 --> 15:20.044
Yeah, everything's fine.

15:20.047 --> 15:21.546
Well, if everything's fine, why you leaving

15:21.548 --> 15:23.079
practice early and
disrespecting your coach?

15:23.081 --> 15:25.682
I told him that I needed to help
Khalil with his physical therapy,

15:25.684 --> 15:26.983
and he still tried to make me stay.

15:26.985 --> 15:28.404
[JEFFERSON] Look, we know
you've been through a lot,

15:28.406 --> 15:30.920
but with school, track, helping Khalil,

15:30.922 --> 15:33.056
your mother and I think you have
a little too much on your plate.

15:33.058 --> 15:35.492
So, maybe you should spend
less time with Khalil,

15:35.495 --> 15:37.726
and more time on school and yourself.

15:37.729 --> 15:39.906
Dad, Khalil needs me.

15:39.909 --> 15:42.232
The reason his mom can't
be there for his rehab is

15:42.234 --> 15:44.500
she's taking extra shifts to
pay for his hospital bills.

15:44.502 --> 15:46.603
Khalil has nurses 24/7.

15:46.605 --> 15:47.870
Okay, look,

15:49.674 --> 15:51.841
we feel really bad about
what happened to Khalil.

15:51.843 --> 15:54.244
We do. But you are our first concern.

15:54.246 --> 15:56.695
You are apologizing
to your coach tomorrow.

15:56.698 --> 15:58.067
[SIGHS]

15:58.070 --> 16:00.578
- I don't wanna run track anymore.
- [JEFFERSON] What?

16:00.581 --> 16:02.785
No, no. You're just saying
that because you're upset.

16:02.787 --> 16:04.164
